    "In reality, what commonly happens is that incorrectly predicted or abnormal training instances appear highly influential to all test instances (Sui et al., 2021).",
    "Barshan et al. (2020) describe such training instances as globally influential.",
    "However, globally influential training instances provide very limited insight into individual model predictions.",
    "As Barshan et al. (2020) note, locally influential training instances are generally much more relevant and insightful when analyzing specific predictions.",
